Schiffspropeller
A three-bladed ship propeller, depicted in dark gray to black.

Strömungslinien
Colored lines representing the flow of a fluid (likely water) around the propeller.<SEP>Mehrfarbige Linien, die den Verlauf einer Strömung in einem Zylinderkopf darstellen.<SEP>Mehrfarbige Linien, die um den Flügel und das Triebwerk herum verlaufen.

Strömungssimulation
A computer simulation showing the flow of a fluid around a rotating ship propeller.<SEP>Strömungssimulation is a simulation of fluid flow, likely analyzed using ANSYS software.<SEP>A visualized flow simulation within the pipe system, showing different velocities or properties.<SEP>Strömungssimulation is a simulation of fluid dynamics, specifically computational fluid dynamics (CFD).

Wirbelbildung
The formation of vortices behind the propeller blades.

Beschleunigung
The propeller accelerates the fluid (water) and directs it in a specific direction.

Auto
The car is depicted as a 3D model or simulation with aerodynamic features.

Luftstrom
The airflow is simulated around the car, represented by color-gradated lines.

Simulation
The simulation is a computer-based representation of the airflow around a moving car.

Aerodynamik
Aerodynamics is the study of the interaction between air and solid objects, such as cars.<SEP>Die Studie der Luftströmung um Objekte, insbesondere in Bezug auf Druckverteilung und Wirbelbildung.

Ansys
Ansys is a software company that provides engineering simulation solutions.<SEP>Ansys is a software company that provides numerical simulation solutions, used to create the image.

Velocity Streamline1
Velocity Streamline1 refers to the visualization of fluid flow velocity in a streamlines representation.<SEP>Velocity Streamline1 refers to the visualized velocity streamlines in the image.

Düse
The Düse (nozzle) is the central object in the image, which tapers from a wider to a narrower cross-section and then widens again.

ANSYS
ANSYS is a company that provides simulation software used for various analyses, including fluid dynamics.<SEP>ANSYS is a software company used for simulation and analysis, specifically for the flow simulation in the image.<SEP>ANSYS is a software company that provides engineering simulation and analysis tools, including ANSYS Fluent for fluid dynamics and heat transfer analysis.<SEP>Eine Firma, die Software für Ingenieursimulationen entwickelt, erkennbar am Logo im Bild.<SEP>ANSYS is a software company whose product was used for the simulation.

Kreisförmige Anordnung von Pfeilen
Kreisförmige Anordnung von Pfeilen represents a circular arrangement of arrows indicating fluid flow or movement.

Zwei kleine Ellipsen
Zwei kleine Ellipsen are small ellipses that could represent inlets or outlets of the fluid flow.

Koordinatensystem
Koordinatensystem is a three-dimensional coordinate system used for spatial reference.

Kühlkörper/Heizkörper
A Kühlkörper/Heizkörper is a technical object used for heat transfer or temperature regulation, characterized by its elongated, ribbed structure.

Achsenkreuz
An Achsenkreuz is a small coordinate system used to indicate spatial orientation in 3D space.

Farbcodierungsskala
A Farbcodierungsskala is a color-coded scale used to represent temperature values, ranging from red (warm) to blue (cold).

Level1 Static Temperature
Level1 Static Temperature refers to a static temperature distribution, likely related to the thermal analysis of the Kühlkörper/Heizkörper.

Temperaturwerte
Temperaturwerte are temperature values measured in degrees Celsius, associated with specific colors on the Farbcodierungsskala.

Rotor
The rotor is a blue object with shovel-like structures, presumed to be rotating and influencing the flow in the channel.

Channel/Pipe
The channel or pipe is a rectangular structure containing the rotating object and through which the fluid flows.

Flow Lines
The flow lines are green lines representing the flow of fluid around the rotating object.

Color Palette
The color palette visualizes the speed of the flow, with different colors representing different velocities.

Coordinate System
The coordinate system is a small grid in the lower right corner, likely used for measurement and reference.

Velocity
Velocity refers to the speed of the fluid flow, measured in meters per second (m/s).

Flow Simulation
A visualized flow simulation within the pipe system, showing different velocities or properties.<SEP>The flow simulation is a computer-aided analysis of fluid dynamics, showing how the rotating object affects the flow.

Computational Fluid Dynamics (CFD)
Computational Fluid Dynamics (CFD) is a category of numerical methods used to solve fluid dynamics problems.<SEP>Eine Methode zur Simulation von Strömungen um Objekte.

Centrifugal Pump
A centrifugal pump is a type of pump that uses a rotating impeller to increase the pressure and flow rate of a fluid.

Radial Fan
A radial fan is a type of fan that uses a rotating impeller to increase the pressure and flow rate of a fluid.

Pressure Distribution
Pressure distribution refers to the variation of pressure across a surface or within a fluid.

Velocity Distribution
Velocity distribution refers to the variation of velocity across a surface or within a fluid.

STUDENT
STUDENT refers to a version of the Ansys software likely used for educational purposes.

Temperature Distribution
Temperature Distribution refers to the display of temperature values across the cylindrical body in the image.

Cylindrical Body
Cylindrical Body is a long, cylindrical object (likely a pipe or rod) shown in the image with a temperature distribution.

Color Scale
Color Scale is a scale on the left side of the image that displays temperature values in Kelvin (K).

YouTube
YouTube is a video-sharing platform where tutorials and educational content, such as the ANSYS Fluent tutorial, are shared.

ANSYS FLUENT
ANSYS Fluent is a computational fluid dynamics (CFD) software used for fluid flow, heat transfer, and mass transport simulations.

Spiralförmige (helikale) Rohrschlange
The spiral-shaped pipe coil is a geometric configuration used for heat transfer analysis in fluid dynamics.

Pressure Contour
Pressure Contour refers to a type of visualization used to represent pressure values across a surface or in a fluid.

Fluid Heat Transfer Analysis
Fluid Heat Transfer Analysis is a study area within engineering that deals with the transfer of heat in fluids, crucial for designing and optimizing systems.

ANSYS2020 R1
ANSYS2020 R1 refers to a specific version of the ANSYS software suite, likely used for the simulation.

Zylinderkopf
Ein Schnittmodell eines Zylinderkopfes eines Verbrennungsmotors, das Ventile, Brennraum und Kanäle zeigt.

Farbskala
A vertical color scale is located on the left side of the image, representing pressure values.<SEP>Eine farbliche Darstellung einer physikalischen Größe, vermutlich Geschwindigkeit oder Druck, mit Farben von Blau (niedrig) bis Rot (hoch).

Verwirbelung
Eine Verwirbelung im Brennraum, die für eine gute Vermischung von Kraftstoff und Luft wichtig ist.

Rohrleitungssystem
A complex 3D model of a pipe system with a horizontal main pipe and a vertical branch.

Farblegende
A vertical color legend ranging from blue (low) to red (high), associated with velocity magnitude.

Dialogfenster
A dialog box from a flow simulation software, containing input fields and options.

Datenvisualisierung
The use of color legends and pipe system coloring to visually represent numerical data (velocity values).

Software-Interaktion
The interaction with software to configure or analyze simulation results.

Pipe System
A complex 3D model of a pipe system with a horizontal main pipe and a vertical branch.

Color Legend
A vertical color legend ranging from blue (low) to red (high), associated with velocity magnitude.

Dialog Box
A dialog box from a flow simulation software, containing input fields and options.

Data Visualization
The use of color legends and pipe system coloring to visually represent numerical data (velocity values).

Software Interaction
The interaction with software to configure or analyze simulation results.

Rohr
not in entity types

Rotorschaufeln
not in entity types

Total Pressure
Total Pressure is a category for measuring the pressure of the fluid flow.

Velocity Magnitude
The color legend represents the velocity magnitude of the flow.<SEP>Velocity Magnitude is a category for measuring the speed of the fluid flow.

Flugzeugflügel
Ein Teil eines Flugzeugflügels ist deutlich zu sehen, einschließlich eines Teils der Tragfläche.

Triebwerk
Ein Triebwerk (vermutlich ein Turbofan) ist unter dem Flügel montiert.

Venturirohr/Düse
The central object is a pipe with a narrowing in the middle (Venturi shape), consisting of a wide initial section, a narrowing in the middle, and an expanding end section.

Abstandsanzeige
A horizontal bar is located at the bottom of the image, labeled with 0,000 m, 1,000 m, and 2,000 m, indicating a length measurement or scale.

Pressure1
A label confirming that the color representation visualizes pressure.

Venturi Effect
The Venturi effect is a phenomenon where the pressure of a fluid decreases as it flows through a constricted section of a pipe.
